The paper deals with the problem of cost sharing in two-sided markets, which is a topic that falls under the field of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also involves the design of mechanisms to maximize welfare, which is a topic in mechanism design (cs.MA). The use of an intermediary platform to match buyers to sellers suggests that the paper may also involve algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and incentive compatibility suggests that it may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
